article.headline: Wagner 72, Yale 65
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- James Ulrich had 21 points and 10 rebounds to help Wagner beat Yale 72-65 on Saturday, snapping the Seahawks' losing streak at three and extending the Bulldogs' skid to five. Jamal Smith and Mark Porter each added 14 points for the Seahawks (2-5). Casey Hughes and Caleb Holmes each scored 11 points for Yale (1-5), which held a 35-31 advantage at halftime. Eric Flato added 10 points. Ross Morin's free throws gave the Bulldogs their biggest lead, 39-31 early in the second half. Wagner responded with an 8-0 run, four by Llewchean Radford, to tie it at 39. The closely contested game saw Hughes pull Yale even at 63 on a jumper with 2:16 to go. Ulrich's basket with 1:56 left ignited a 9-2 run that closed out the game.
